				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">you'll have to bend the sram pins backwards to "mirror" the chip.  
<br />
<br />Your schematic is basically the pin out for the MMC3 on kevtris' NES cart types doc.
<br />
<br />I have my own scratch diagrams but they are really nothing other than pinouts.  That's all there really is to the schematic unless you want an illegible rat's nest.
<br />
<br />If you're not to sure about it all I would recommend grabbing a multimeter and tracing out your own version of the two boards and be sure to use kevtris' doc as a reference.  Then you'll be able to make sense of everything for yourself and actually have a chance at getting it to work.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

