				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Like I said awhile back, the only real way to do this without using a TLSROM board is to basically solder the SRAM to the bottom side of the PRG ROM chip.
<br />
<br />You'll have to bend all the pins 'UP' vice they way they normally point 'DOWN'.  You'll basically mirror the chip and then you'll be able to get all the Data bits, lower address bits, and maybe /CE to match up with the PRG ROM.  It won't be every single pin especially the power pin and /WE, but you'll have most of them match up.
<br />
<br />You'd basically create a sandwich with the PRG ROM and WRAM as bread with the board in the middle as the meat...</div>

