				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Kevtris' nes cart types is your best resource.  If you've got a copy of SMB3 or some other TSROM (I mispoke eariler) game you can always reference that.  
<br />
<br />The ALL the WRAM address and data lines connect to the same data/address line on the PRG ROM.  the only things controlled by the mapper are the /CE, CE, and /WE.  they go to pins 30, 41, 42 on the MMC3 if you go by the pin numbering on kevtris' doc.
<br />
<br />As for the PRG ROM nothing should be any different.  You just have to match up the old pin out to your new ROM.</div>

